President Obama has announced his intent to appoint three individuals to key Administration posts in the Nuclear Waste Technical Review Board. The appointees are Dr. Sue Clark, a Regents Professor of Chemistry at Washington State University; Dr. Rod Ewing, a Distinguished University Professor in the Department of Geological Sciences at the University of Michigan; and Dr. Linda Nozick, a Professor of Civil and Environmental Engineering at Cornell University. These individuals bring extensive experience and expertise in their respective fields and will serve the American people in these important roles.